HEADWORD: Guidance
<hw>Guid"ance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Guide</er>.]</ety> <def>The act or result of guiding; the
superintendence or assistance of a guide; direction; government; a
leading.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q> His studies were without <qex>guidance</qex> and without
plan.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Guide</ent>⟦br⟧
